# TimeGift Development Rules

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript for type safety
- Prefer functional components and hooks
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Follow Next.js 15 App Router conventions

## State Management
- Use React hooks for local state
- Zustand for global state (if needed)
- Supabase for backend state

## Database
- All queries through Supabase client
- Use RLS policies for security
- Server components for data fetching when possible

## Security
- Never expose service_role key in client code
- Always validate user permissions
- Use RLS policies for data access control

## Performance
- Use Server Components by default
- Client Components only when needed (interactivity)
- Optimize images with Next.js Image component
- Lazy load heavy components

## File Organization
- `/app` - Pages and routes
- `/components` - Reusable React components  
- `/lib` - Core utilities and configurations
- `/utils` - Helper functions
- `/types` - TypeScript type definitions

## Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `GiftCard.tsx`)
- Files: kebab-case (e.g., `gift-card.tsx`)
- Functions: camelCase (e.g., `sendGift()`)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE

## Git Commits & Deployment
- Use conventional commits format
- feat: new feature
- fix: bug fix
- docs: documentation
- style: formatting
- refactor: code restructuring
- test: adding tests

## Automatic Deployment Workflow
**CRITICAL: After every code change, you MUST:**
1. Commit all changes with descriptive message
2. Push to GitHub (main branch)
3. Deploy to timegift.6x7.gr via Vercel

**Deployment Steps:**
```bash
# 1. Commit and push
cd "/Users/phktistakis/Devoloper Projects/TimeGift"
git add -A
git commit -m "Descriptive commit message"
git push origin HEAD:main

# 2. Deploy to Vercel (if Vercel CLI available)
cd timegift-app
vercel --prod

# OR trigger Vercel deployment via GitHub (automatic if connected)
# Vercel auto-deploys on push to main branch
```

**Always verify:**
- Changes are committed and pushed
- Deployment is triggered (check Vercel dashboard)
- Site is live at https://timegift.6x7.gr

## API Routes
- Use Next.js Route Handlers
- Validate inputs
- Return proper HTTP status codes
- Handle errors gracefully

## Testing
- Test critical flows
- Mock Supabase calls
- Test dark/light mode compatibility
- Test responsive design
